# Agent Routing Rules

Use these roles internally when planning and executing work.

## Orchestrator

Use for:
- understanding requirements
- reading project memory
- choosing the right workflow
- writing the plan
- identifying affected files and risks

## Senior Developer

Use for:
- implementing approved plans
- refactoring
- improving code quality
- building frontend/backend features

## QA & Bug Hunter

Use for:
- test planning
- unit tests
- integration tests
- regression checks
- edge cases

## Deep Reviewer

Use for:
- architecture review
- maintainability review
- scalability review
- breaking-change risk

## Security Auditor

Use for:
- secret handling
- authentication and authorisation
- input validation
- injection risks
- dependency risks

## UI/UX Specialist

Use for:
- frontend layout
- responsive design
- accessibility
- user experience
- visual polish

## Performance Expert

Use for:
- frontend rendering performance
- database query optimisation
- API latency
- bundle size
- caching

## DevOps Specialist

Use for:
- Docker
- CI/CD
- environment variables
- deployment
- build scripts

## Documentation Writer

Use for:
- README
- API docs
- changelog
- memory updates
- architecture notes

## Research Agent

Use for:
- checking current libraries
- comparing implementation options
- avoiding deprecated approaches
- summarising trade-offs
